data.description: Nestled amidst a tranquil setting, this exquisite 4-bedroom, 3.5-bathroom residence exudes elegance and sophistication, catering to a discerning lifestyle. The open floor plan seamlessly blends the living room, dining area, and kitchen, fostering a warm and inviting ambiance. At the heart of the home lies the eat in kitchen, boasting a sprawling island with ample counter space, custom cabinets, top-of-the-line appliances, and sleek granite countertops, and large walk in pantry, transforming culinary endeavors into a delightful experience.  Dining area is Flex space since there is 2nd Dining area in kitchen. The downstairs master suite offers a sanctuary of tranquility, featuring a luxurious ensuite bathroom with a soothing soaking tub, a spacious walk-in closet, and ample natural light. For those seeking cinematic thrills, the media room emerges as the ultimate entertainment haven, equipped with surround sound, a state-of-the-art projector and screen, and a wet bar perfect for hosting unforgettable gatherings. Hardwood floors and large tiles grace the home's interior, adding a touch of refinement and warmth underfoot. The expansive loft provides a versatile space for relaxation, play, or creative pursuits. To ensure the utmost comfort and convenience, a water softener system safeguards the home's plumbing, while an automatic sprinkler system maintains a lush and verdant landscape.  In backyard, a sturdy stone fence exudes an air of privacy and security, while also enhancing the home's timeless aesthetic appeal. This exceptional residence epitomizes luxury and functionality, offering a haven of comfort and style for discerning homeowners.  Walking distance to community pool and amenities. In sought after Schertz-Cibolo-UC ISD and 6 miles to Randolph, quick access to I35 and shopping. Water softener and refrigerator convey.
